[Student "S"]
{With only 4 points you make a Negative 2\D response to partner's 2\C opener. He now bids 2NT. What is your bid? 

True, 4 points isn't much. But added to partner's 22-24 it becomes enough for a game. Your problem isn't whether to bid to the game or not, (you definitely will), but whether you should use Stayman to find out if there is a 4-4 \S fit. You decide not to do this because your 4-3-3-3 distribution removes the possibility of you getting any ruffs. So you bid 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
